  "response": "It's never too late to learn computer programming. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Age is not a barrier\n- People of all ages can learn programming\n- Many successful programmers started later in life\n- Online resources make learning more accessible than ever\n\n2. Advantages of learning at different ages\n- Young people: Typically quicker learning, more free time\n- Older learners: More discipline, life experience, clearer goals\n- Mid-career professionals: Often have better focus and motivation\n\n3. Learning strategies\n- Start with beginner-friendly languages (Python, JavaScript)\n- Use online courses (Codecademy, Udemy, edX)\n- Watch YouTube tutorials\n- Join coding bootcamps\n- Practice consistently\n\n4. Realistic expectations\n- Learning takes time and patience\n- Start with basic concepts\n- Don't get discouraged\n- Focus on steady progress\n\n5. Career opportunities\n- Programming skills valuable in many fields\n- Remote work options\n- Good salary potential\n- Continuous learning environment\n\n6. Additional benefits\n- Enhances problem-solving skills\n- Boosts cognitive abilities\n- Provides creative outlet\n- Potential for freelance or entrepreneurial work\n\nRemember: Motivation and consistent practice are more important than age.",
